# Changelog Update Rule

**EVERY time you push to git, you MUST update BOTH changelog files in the same commit:**

## 1. `frontend/src/data/changelog.js` (UI-facing)
- Bump `APP_VERSION` (e.g. 2.9.3 → 2.9.4)
- Add new entry at the TOP of `CHANGELOG` array:
```js
{
  version: "X.Y.Z",
  date: "Апрель 2026",
  badge: "new" | "fix" | null,
  changes: [
    "Short Russian description of each change",
    ...
  ]
}
```
- `badge: "new"` for features, `badge: "fix"` for bugfixes, `null` for mixed/refactor

## 2. `CHANGELOG.md` (developer history, root of project)
- Add new section at the TOP under the date heading
- Include commit hash, file paths changed, and bullet descriptions

## Commit format
Include both files in the same commit as the feature/fix:
```
git add frontend/src/data/changelog.js CHANGELOG.md <other files>
git commit -m "vX.Y.Z: short description"
```

## ⚠️ NEVER push without updating both changelog files first.
